I wrote two new templates {{tl|Print version of module}} and {{tl|Print version of module notice}}, together with a new [[:Category:Modules with print version]] (subcategory of [[:Category:Print Versions]]). As mentioned before, I think I'm flooding the [[:Category:Books with print version]] with the printable versions of lessons of the wikibook [[Spanish by Choice]]. To avoid this (and since the new printing possibilities don't work well for these lessons), I'm now using these two new templates for modules of that wikibook; thus, they don't appear in [[:Category:Books with print version]] (at least they won't appear after caches are updated; this might take some time). Of course, everyone may still use the templates {{tl|Print version}} and {{tl|Print version notice}} for modules. The new templates and category just offer a way to avoid flooding of the [[:Category:Books with print version]] with printable modules. Is this OK? --[[User:Martin Kraus|Martin Kraus]] ([[User talk:Martin Kraus|talk]]) 09:57, 26 November 2008 (UTC)

